content.description: Start matched at small shoulder level crimps. Trend right on positive incut rails and crimps. Tricky and committing moves on the arete for the finish.
content.protection: Sits on a sloping hill. Good pad coverage and spotters to prevent rolling further downhill would be ideal.
content.location: 50ft uphill on the west side of the pullout. Can be seen from the road and Jabba Boulder

content.description: Sit start the short arete with a small right gaston and left hand squeezing the edge of the boulder. Move up the arete to summit the capstone.
content.location: Up right of Vegan Shoveler. Looks taller in the guide book .

content.description: Holds are just good enough to pull on, feet stay decent throughout. Crux seems to be attaining the crack feature near the top of the rock.
content.protection: A couple pads and a spotter don't hurt at this height
content.location: Big mossy boulder right off the road just downhill from Vegan shoveler. The face climb is pointed away from the road if coming up the mountain. Start on first obvious hand holds and pull feet off the ground. Goes straight up the middle of the tall face.
